Lagos State governor, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu, at the weekend declared that attracting local and direct foreign investment to accelerate growth of the state remains the major focus of his administration’s policies. Sanwo-Olu stated this on the one-year anniversary of its Alaro City launch in Lekki Free Zone and the unveiling of a new wave of investments in Lagos State, with the commencement of operations of Ariel Foods, a multinational therapeutic food producer. He pointed out that the event affirms the status of Lagos as one of the leading and preferred investment destinations in Africa, saying the state will continue to welcome local and foreign investors to partner with it in their quest to deliver a Lagos that works for all of us. The governor said, ”As a public private partnership between Rendeavour and the Lagos State Government; our goal is for Alaro City to become a veritable model for PPPs of this kind. ‘’We also intend for it to serve as a model for the kind of reasonably-priced and climate-friendly urban developments that Lagos deserves, as a 21st century megacity. ‘’We will do this by continuing to implement policies,  regulations and incentives that expand the space for the private sector to thrive. Experience has shown very clearly that there is no limit to the value created when government and private sector play to their various strengths.” Lagos State will continue to be fully alive to all of its responsibilities.  